name: Alfredo Chicken Wings
author: Anonymous
summary: These wings take a finger-licking good crowd favorite and raise them up a notch with a buttery Alfredo sauce.
ingredients: ¼ cup LAND O LAKES® Salted Butter
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Grease a large rimmed baking sheet
Place wings on prepared baking sheet
Sprinkle with seasoned salt; mix to evenly season the wings
Bake in preheated oven until crisp and cooked through, about 1 hour
Turn on oven broiler; finish the wings under the broiler to crisp both sides, about 1 minute per side
Melt butter over medium-low heat in a small saucepan
Add cream and garlic stirring until small bubbles form
Add grated cheese and continue to stir until well blended
